{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0652c2bda05ebb7f63d5112cd7ca94ff","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The likely untested failure mode: **`--bare --resume <session_id>` together**.\n\n### Why it's untested\n\n`consultCluster` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:94-99`) always creates a new session — it never passes `resumeSessionId`:\n```ts\nconst response = claude.runPromptWithOptions\n  ? await claude.runPromptWithOptions(buildClusterQuestionPrompt(input.question), {\n      ...profilePromptOptions(profileSelection.selected),\n      appendSystemPrompt: buildClusterSystemPrompt(loaded)\n    })\n  : await claude.runPrompt(...)\n```\n\nAnd `CliClaudeAdapter` (`src/claude.ts:50-64`) only adds `--resume` when `options.resumeSessionId` is set, which `consultCluster` never provides. So we have no coverage for the combination.\n\n### What could go wrong\n\n- `--bare` may create sessions with auth state that can't be resumed with `--resume` (bare sessions may use a different auth handshake)\n- The `.jsonl` file format when created with `--bare` may be incompatible with `--resume` — the resume path may silently produce degraded output or fail mid-stream\n- When Phase 5 (`--fork-session --resume <baseline>`) is implemented, this silent incompatibility would produce wrong answers rather than errors\n\n### How to detect it\n\nAdd a resume-capable probe using the existing fixture session (`src/claude.ts:124-131`):\n```ts\n// In probeProfile — test bare with resume separately from bare alone\nif (profile === \"bare\" && fixtureSessionId) {\n  try {\n    await claude.runPromptWithOptions(\"ping\", {\n      resumeSessionId: fixtureSessionId,\n      extraArgs: [\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"],\n      includeConfiguredExtraArgs: false\n    });\n    // bare+resume works\n  } catch (error) {\n    return { available: false, duration_ms: 0, error: `bare+resume failed: ${error.message}` };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nTrack it as a separate capability alongside `bare.available` — if bare+resume fails but bare alone succeeds, surface the delta so operators know before a Phase 5 fork silently produces bad results."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":187,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3056,"cache_read_input_tokens":97643},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e168c3-f7d3-48fb-8e86-0c3c3b4ba74a","uuid":"c0d3e68f-1818-47ea-978f-92029d9a952f"}
